TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {74390=After Phil Dawson kicked a 41-yard field goal to put the Browns up 20-17, the Jaguars got the ball back with 2:46 remaining with a chance for the win., 76225=Cleveland had a chance to extend its lead with 8:05 left in the half, but Dawson's 51-yard field goal attempt went wide right., 77257=The Jaguars then evened the game with 3:34 left. Following Dawson's miss, Jacksonville advanced to the Cleveland 14 before Garrard connected with Lewis in the middle of the end zone for the receiver's eighth TD of the season., 73333=Maurice Jones-Drew rushed for 132 yards on 24 carries, including the go- ahead score with 1:16 remaining, to help lift the Jaguars (6-4) to their third straight win., 74553=They started the drive at their own 13-yard line, but on the third play, Garrard connected with Jones-Drew for a short screen pass that the running back took 75 yards to the Cleveland one. After Rashad Jennings failed to punch it in, Jones-Drew went up the middle to give Jacksonville the 24-20 lead with 1:16 left on the clock.}
